com.w2.api.engine.components.commands

Class HeadPosition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.w2.api.engine.components.commands.HeadPosition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RobotCommand, RobotComponent

    public class HeadPosition
extends java.lang.Object
implements RobotCommand
    The HeadPosition objects sets the Robot head position horizontally or vertically.

    Negative command values represent left (horizontal) or up (vertical). Positive command values represents right (horizontally) or down (vertically).

    Horizontal head position values have the following valid ranges: -2.094 to 2.094 in radians or -120.0 to 120.0 in degrees. Vertical head position values have the following ranges: -0.349 to 0.131 in radians or -20 to 7.5 in degrees.
